Lumber futures fell for losses of asmuch as 3.50 dlrs per tbf, basis May, after starting 0.80 lowerto 0.10 higher.    Lack of carryover demand and pressure associated with thelower trend to financial futures early touched off some stoploss orders. Futures fell to near technical support beforerecovering slightly, traders said.    Some pressure also stemmed from a quiet cash market anderroding cash prices, they said.    Commission houses and locals sold on the break and offsetscale-down buying by GNP, they added. Reuter&#3;